bufrtest.py - prints the values of 1 or more BUFR mnemonics to the terminal. 
              The script must be editted for the mnemonics to be retrieved.

  Usage:
    bufrtest.py <BUFR file>

    <BUFR file> is the full pathname of the BUFR file to retrieve data from

  Example:
    bufrtest.py /scratch1/NCEPDEV/global/glopara/dump/gdas.20210101/12/gdas.t12z.satwnd.tm00.bufr_d


bufrpeek.py - outputs the values for a single mnemonic or sequence for a
              subset type to stdout. Optionally writes the output to an
              ASCII (text) file or a netCDF file (can only choose 1 option).
              Requires bufrtblstruc.py and bufrTableTools.py

  Usage:
    bufrpeek.py <BUFR file> <subset type> [-o <ASCII file> | -n <netCDF file>]
    If -o and -n are both specified, -o will override -n

    <BUFR file> is the full pathname of the BUFR file to retrieve data from
    <subset type> is the subset (or observation) type to retrieve data for
    <ASCII file> (optional) is the name of an ASCII (text) file to write the
                            output to
    <netCDF file> (optional) is the name of an netCDF file to write the
                             output to

  Example:
    bufrpeek.py /scratch1/NCEPDEV/global/glopara/dump/gdas.20210101/12/gdas.t12z.satwnd.tm00.bufr_d NC005044


bufrmnemonic.py - outputs a map of the BUFR mnemonic hierarchy from a
                  set of tables in a BUFR file to stdtout. Optionally writes
                  the output to an ASCII (text) file. Requires 
                  bufrtblstruc.py and bufrTableTools.py

  Usage:
    bufrmnemonicmap.py <BUFR file> <subset type> [-o <ASCII file> 
    If -o and -n are both specified, -o will override -n

    <BUFR file> is the full pathname of the BUFR file to create a mnemonic
                map for
    <subset type> is the subset (or observation) type to create a map for
    <ASCII file> (optional) is the name of an ASCII (text) file to write the
                            output to

  Example:
    bufrmnemonicmap.py /scratch1/NCEPDEV/global/glopara/dump/gdas.20210101/12/gdas.t12z.satwnd.tm00.bufr_d NC005044


validateSatwndsConv.py - compares the values for all fields in an IODA
                         netCDF file with the values in the BUFR file that
                         it was created from and writes a report. Requires
                         the YAML file that was used to create the IODA file.
                         Requires bufrtblstruc.py, bufrTableTools.py, and
                         BUFRMsgTypeToYAML.py. BUFRMsgTypeToYAML.py
                         needs to be editted when validateSatwndsConv.py
                         is used on different BUFR message types.

  Usage:
    validateSatwndsConv.py <BUFR file> <subset type> <IODA netCDF file> [-y <YAML directory>]

    <BUFR file> is the full pathname of the BUFR file to retrieve data from
    <subset type> is the subset (or observation) type to retrieve data for
    <IODA netCDF file> is the full pathname of the IODA netCDF file
    <YAML directory> (optional) is the directory that the YAML file used to create the IODA netCDF file is in. Default is the current working directory.

  Example:
    validateSatwndsConv.py /scratch1/NCEPDEV/global/glopara/dump/gdas.20210101/12/gdas.t12z.satwnd.tm00.bufr_d NC005044 /home/Jeffrey.Smith/ioda_check/NC005044.nc -y /home/Jeffrey.Smith/ioda_check/yaml_files


bufrtblstruc.py - writes the tables for the specified subset type from a
                  BUFR file to stdout

  Usage:
    bufrtablstruc.py <BUFR file> <subset type>

      <BUFR file> is the full pathname of a BUFR file
      <subset type> is the subset (observation) type to retrieve the tables for

  Example:
    bufrtblstruc.py /scratch1/NCEPDEV/global/glopara/dump/gdas.20210101/12/gdas.t12z.satwnd.tm00.bufr_d NC005044